The paper involves a Bayesian game theoretic framework to study the impact of social learning on users' data reporting strategies and devise the payment mechanism for the data collector accordingly. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves a learning framework. Additionally, the paper involves game theory (cs.GT) and privacy (cs.CR) which are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it discusses the information content of the reported data. Finally, the paper involves social interactions (cs.SI) which is another likely sub-category.
